reviewText: This is an incredibly engrossing series. Subjects are celebrities in one way or another (Olympic champions, writers, actors, singers) but as they follow the leads and find out about their family history they become equally fascinated in how their ancestors lived. My mom and I have been watching the British version since season 1. Anyone who is interested in genealogy should try a set. I don't think you will be disappointed. The equally-engaging American series is only out for season 1 and 2 I believe. VERY highly recommended.
